org.magnos.net
Interface Pipeline

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractPipeline, TcpPipeline, TcpPipeline, UdpPipeline
public interface Pipeline

A pipeline creates servers and clients and defines the protocols and default listeners the servers and client utilize.

Author:
Philip Diffenderfer

Method Detail

newServer

Server newServer()
Creates a new Server. If there is an error creating the server, null will be returned. The default ServerListener will be added to the server if non-null.

Returns:
The reference to the newly created server, or null.

newClient

Client newClient()
Creates a new Client for connecting to servers with. If there is an error creating the client, null will be returned. The default ClientListener will be added to the client if non-null.

Returns:
The reference to the newly created client, or null.

newClient

Client newClient(Server server)
Creates a new Client for a server implementation. If there is an error creating the client, null will be returned. The default ClientListener will be added to the client if non-null.

Parameters:
server - The server the client is for.
Returns:
The reference to the newly created client, or null.

getServers

java.util.Set<Server> getServers()
Returns the set of open servers created by this pipeline. This set should not be modified and is not thread safe, it is only meant for iterating the set of servers.

Returns:
The reference to a set of open servers.
See Also:
ConcurrentSet

Returns:
The reference to a set of open clients.

ConcurrentSet

getDefaultProtocol

java.lang.Class<?> getDefaultProtocol()
Returns the default protocol data type. This is the first protocol clients of pipeline use to read data until its changed.

Returns:
The reference to the default protocol.

setDefaultProtocol

void setDefaultProtocol(java.lang.Class<?> type)
Sets the default protocol data type. This is the first protocol clients of pipeline use to read data until its changed.

Parameters:
type - The default protocol.

addProtocol

<D> void addProtocol(Protocol<D> protocol)
Adds the protocol to the pipeline. A protocol is mapped by a class type, when a client has to read data it queries its pipeline with its current protocol type and proceeds to decode read data.

Type Parameters:
D - The data type encoded and decoded by the protocol.
Parameters:
protocol - The protocol to use to encode and decode the given data type.

getSelector

Selector getSelector()
Returns the selector used by the pipeline to allocate workers for clients and acceptors for servers. This is also used by the servers to create workers to handle clients unless changed explicitly for a given server.

Returns:
The reference to the Selector.

setSelector

void setSelector(Selector selector)
Sets the selector used by the pipeline to allocate workers for clients and acceptors for servers. This is also used by the servers to create workers to handle clients unless changed explicitly for a given server.

Parameters:
selector - The new selector of the pipeline.

getProtocol

<D> Protocol<D> getProtocol(java.lang.Class<D> type)
Gets the protocol associated with the given class.

Type Parameters:
D - The data type encoded and decoded by the protocol.
Parameters:
type - The class of the data type.
Returns:
The reference to the protocol which encodes and decodes the given data type.

getClientListener

ClientListener getClientListener()
Returns the default ClientListener for clients created with this pipeline. If this is non-null and a ClientListener is not specified on connect this will be added to the clients listener list.

Returns:
The reference to the default ClientListener.

setClientListener

void setClientListener(ClientListener listener)
Sets the default ClientListener for clients created with this pipeline. If this is non-null and a ClientListener is not specified on connect this will be added to the client's listener list.

Parameters:
listener - The default ClientListener.

getServerListener

ServerListener getServerListener()
Returns the default ServerListener for servers created with this pipeline. If this is non-null and a ServerListener is not specified on listen this will be added to the servers listener list.

Returns:
The reference to the default ServerListener.

setServerListener

void setServerListener(ServerListener listener)
Sets the default ServerListener for servers created with this pipeline. If this is non-null and a ServerListener is not specified on listen this will be added to the server's listener list.

Parameters:
listener - The default ServerListener.
